0for%20retirement%2C%20and%20if%20you%20expect%20it%20to%20be%20similar%20to%20your%20current%20day-to-day%20life%2C%20you%20have%20to%20plan%20ahead.%20He%20shared%20the%20four%20most%20important%20factors%20that%20enable%20his%20clients%20to%20retire%20early%20without%20making%20a%20big%20lifestyle%20change.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Pay%20close%20attention%20to%20your%20spending%20habits%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20easy%20first%20step%20toward%20planning%20for%20early%20retirement%20is%20doing%20a%20deep-dive%20into%20your%20spending%20habits.%20Pelham%20said%20that%20people%20are%20usually%20surprised%20at%20the%20different%20opportunities%20they%20find%20to%20save%20money%20every%20month%2C%20which%20can%20then%20be%20used%20as%20savings%20or%20investments%20to%20help%20with%20retirement%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOf%20course%2C%20if%20you%20buy%20less%20expensive%20clothing%20and%20cars%2C%20that%20would%20make%20a%20difference%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20if%20you're%20trying%20to%20maintain%20your%20lifestyle%2C%20there%20are%20other%20areas%20to%20look%20at.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPelham%20said%20to%20start%20by%20examining%20your%20services%20and%20insurance%20policies.%C2%A0%26quot%3BYou%20might%20get%20a%20discounted%20rate%20for%20consolidating%20these%20services%20under%20one%20provider%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Flife-insurance%2Fbest-life-insurance-companies%5C%22%3ELife%20insurance%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20one%20policy%20that's%20worth%20double-checking%20to%20make%20sure%20you%20have%20the%20best%20price%20for%20the%20level%20of%20coverage%20you%20want%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%26quot%3B%20Additionally%2C%20it's%20worth%20looking%20at%20combining%20homeowners%2C%20auto%2C%20and%20other%20policies%20to%20receive%20discounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20area%20of%20spending%20people%20can%20look%20into%20is%20how%20they%20are%20managing%20to%20pay%20off%20their%20debt.%20%26quot%3BSome%20types%20of%20debt%20might%20even%20be%20tax%20deductible%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BCheck%20to%20see%20if%20you%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-to-consolidate-debt%5C%22%3Econsolidate%20debt%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20get%20lower%20interest%20rates%2C%20or%20change%20terms.%26quot%3B%20You%20may%20want%20to%20have%20a%20financial%20advisor%20or%20accountant%20take%20a%20look%20at%20your%20debt%20to%20help%20you%20strategize.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20Relocate%20to%20an%20area%20with%20a%20lower%20cost%20of%20living%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you've%20felt%20tempted%20to%20change%20where%20you%20live%2C%20Pelham%20recommended%20looking%20into%20relocating%20to%20an%20area%20with%20a%20lower%20cost%20of%20living%20to%20help%20you%20with%20your%20future%20retirement%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20trade%20a%20high%20cost%20of%20living%20location%20for%20a%20lower%20one%2C%20you're%20able%20to%20cut%20your%20expenses%20down%20quite%20a%20bit%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20shared.%20%26quot%3BPlus%2C%20if%20you%20own%20a%20house%2C%20you%20could%20cash%20out%20the%20equity%20once%20it's%20sold%20and%20buy%20a%20less%20expensive%20house%20in%20that%20new%20location%20and%20use%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20cash%20to%20help%20you%20save%20or%20invest%20for%20retirement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20Pelham%20said%20that%20some%20of%20his%20clients%20who%20live%20in%20Miami%20%E2%80%94%20one%20of%20the%20most%20expensive%20cities%20in%20Florida%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%20but%20work%20remotely%2C%20decided%20to%20sell%20their%20house%20and%20move%20to%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20client%20of%20mine%20moved%20to%20Gainesville%2C%20which%20costs%20less%20to%20live%20in%2C%20and%20they%20were%20able%20to%20maintain%20their%20income%2C%20lower%20their%20expenses%2C%20and%20cash%20out%20the%20equity%20from%20their%20homes%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThose%20steps%20could%20help%20position%20them%20to%20retire%20much%20earlier%20than%20they%20originally%20planned.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Take%20a%20close%20look%20at%20your%20asset%20allocation%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20thing%20people%20can%20control%2C%20as%20they%20plan%20for%20early%20retirement%2C%20is%20their%20asset%20allocation%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BLook%20at%20how%20much%20money%20you've%20invested%20in%20different%20categories%20or%20perhaps%20assets%20you%20haven't%20invested%20in%20that%20could%20be%20beneficial%20to%20your%20overall%20portfolio.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20benefit%20of%20this%20exercise%20is%20to%20align%20your%20allocation%20with%20your%20overall%20goals%20and%20timeline%20to%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Pelham%20suggested%20working%20with%20a%20financial%20advisor%20or%20tax%20professional%20who%20can%20help%20you%20optimize%20your%20asset%20allocation%2C%20including%20understanding%20which%20assets%20are%20better%20in%20a%20tax-deferred%20account%20versus%20a%20taxable%20account.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20example%2C%20if%20you're%20saving%20%2420%2C000%20a%20year%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-high-yield-savings-accounts-rates-right-now%5C%22%3Esavings%20account%3C%2Fa%3E%20rather%20than%20in%20a%20401(k)%20plan%2C%20which%20helps%20reduce%20taxable%20income%2C%20that's%20a%20change%20that%20can%20help%20a%20person%20save%20more%20for%20retirement%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20Review%20your%20retirement%20accounts%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20opportunity%20Pelham%20shared%20to%20maximize%20your%20finances%20now%20for%20early%20retirement%20is%20to%20look%20at%20your%20retirement%20accounts.%20He%20often%20sees%20people%20with%20old%20401(k)s%20that%20haven't%20been%20touched%20in%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20people%20who%20have%20worked%20for%20multiple%20different%20employers%20might%20have%20untouched%20401(k)s%20that%20they%20forgot%20about%20or%20didn't%20ever%20combine%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20money%20might%20be%20sitting%20in%20those%20accounts%20on%20autopilot%20without%20any%20type%20of%20investment%20strategy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPelham%20said%20that%20rolling%20those%20older%20401(k)%20funds%20into%20an%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-ira%5C%22%3EIRA%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20provide%20access%20to%20more%20investment%20options%20and%20integrate%20these%20dollars%20into%20your%20overall%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDon't%20know%20where%20to%20start%3F%20Consider%20a%20financial%20advisor.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-to-find-financial-advisor%5C%22%3EFinding%20a%20financial%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20hard.%20SmartAsset's%20free%20tool%20matches%20you%20with%20up%20to%20three%20fiduciary%20financial%20advisors%20that%20serve%20your%20area%20in%20minutes.%20Each%20advisor%20has%20been%20vetted%20by%20SmartAsset%20and%20is%20held%20to%20a%20fiduciary%20standard%20to%20act%20in%20your%20best%20interests.%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26utm_medium%3Dcpc%26utm_campaign%3Dbus__falc_bicontent%26utm_content%3DBI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Start%20your%20search%20now.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretire-early-without-changing-lifestyle-tips-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720180742000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F668590731f0c1cd6d73168d2%3Ff