20country's%20lowest%20growth%20rate%20since%20the%20early%2019th%20century%20and%20a%20steep%20cost-of-living%20increase%2C%20the%20highest%20in%2041%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Cstrong%3EBritish%20economy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20has%20slowed%20significantly%20over%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20even%20accounting%20for%20the%20global%20crisis%20triggered%20by%20the%20Covid%20pandemic.%20GDP%20per%20capita%20grew%20just%204.3%20per%20cent%20from%202007%20to%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20previous%2016%20years%20that%20figure%20was%20a%20massive%2046%20per%20cent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20meant%20incomes%20stagnated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20report%20by%20the%20nonpartisan%20Centres%20for%20Cities%20research%20institute%20indicated%20Britons%2C%20on%20average%2C%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Feconomy%2F2024%2F6%2F26%2F10200-how-much-worse-off-britons-are-after-14-years-of-tory-rule%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A310%2C200%20less%20to%20save%20or%20spend%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%202010%20and%202022%2C%20compared%20to%201998-2010%20growth%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%C2%A0the%20UK's%20national%20debt%20-%20%C2%A32.7%20trillion%20-%20is%20higher%20than%20at%20any%20point%20since%20the%201960s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20did%20seem%20to%20be%20some%20relief%20soon%3B%20in%20May%20the%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20spoke%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bsoft%20landing%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20economy%2C%20and%20upgraded%20the%20growth%20forecast%20by%200.2%20percentage%20points%20to%200.7.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20it%20was%2C%20perhaps%2C%20on%20the%20back%20of%20that%20expectation%20Mr%20Sunak%20called%20for%20the%20early%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Cstrong%3ENHS%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20is%20seen%20by%20many%20to%20be%20the%20crown%20in%20the%20British%20government's%20public%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Add%20image%20caption%20here%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Add%20image%20caption%20here%5C