0dissolution%20of%20parliament%20triggered%20by%20President%20Emmanuel%20Macron%20saw%20a%20dramatic%20rise%20of%20the%20far-right%20National%20Rally%20(RN)%20party%2C%20while%20in%20the%20United%20Kingdom%2C%20the%20Labour%20Party%20won%20by%20an%20unprecedented%20margin%20and%20ended%2014%20years%20of%20Conservative%20rule.%20Both%20elections%20revealed%20voter%20discontent%20in%20the%20two%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Rise%20Of%20The%20Far-Right%20In%20France%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20June%2030%2C%20the%20first%20leg%20of%20the%20French%20elections%20took%20place.%20An%20attempt%20to%20halt%20the%20momentum%20of%20the%20resurgent%20RN%2C%20however%2C%20saw%20Mr%20Macron's%20decision%20to%20dissolve%20parliament%20spectacularly%20backfire.%20RN%2C%20led%20by%20Marine%20Le%20Pen%20won%20the%20highest%20vote%20share%2C%20polling%2033%20per%20cent%2C%20the%20left-wing%20New%20Popular%20Front%20(NFP)%20garnering%2028%20per%20cent%20and%20Mr%20Macron's%20centrist%20bloc%20could%20manage%20only%2020.7%20per%20cent%20in%20votes%20tally.%20This%20result%20set%20the%20stage%20for%20the%20second%20round%20of%20polling%20to%20be%20held%20on%20July%207.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Macron's%20suspension%20of%20parliament%20was%20meant%20to%20solidify%20a%20clear%20majority%20for%20his%20administration%20after%20getting%20heavily%20beaten%20during%20the%20European%20Parliament%20parliament.%20However%2C%20it%20was%20meant%20to%20unify%20opposition%20against%20the%20RN%2C%20but%20it%20seems%20it%20has%20emboldened%20the%20far-right%20instead.%20The%20polls%20correctly%20predicted%20that%20the%20RN%20would%20lead%2C%20and%20Macron's%20approval%20ratings%20collapsed%20to%2036%20per%20cent%2C%20as%20indicated%20by%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Revival%20Of%20Labour%20In%20UK%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAcross%20the%20Channel%2C%20the%20UK%20saw%20its%20own%20political%20earthquake.%20On%20Friday%2C%20Keir%20Starmer's%20Labour%20Party%20surmounted%20the%20odds%20and%20registered%20a%20historic%20win%2C%20ending%20Rishi%20Sunak's%20Conservative%20Party's%2014-year%20rule.%20The%20election%20results%20reflect%20widespread%20dissatisfaction%20with%20the%20Tory%20government%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20Liz%20Truss's%20short-lived%20and%20disastrous%20tenure%20and%20Mr%20Sunak's%20leadership%20in%20its%20aftermath.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Truss's%20brief%20premiership%20of%20only%2049%20days%2C%20which%20was%20marked%20by%20unfunded%20tax%20cuts%20upsetting%20the%20markets%20damaged%20the%20reputation%20of%20the%20Conservative%20Party.%20Mr%20Sunak's%20attempts%20to%20steady%20the%20ship%20were%20insufficient%20to%20regain%20public%20trust.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Starmer's%20leadership%20has%20been%20pivotal%20in%20Labour's%20revival.%20Since%20taking%20up%20the%20role%20in%20early%202020%2C%20he%20has%20repositioned%20the%20party%20to%20the%20centre%2C%20and%20fixed%20problems%20within%20the%20party%20that%20include%20in-fighting%20and%20anti-Semitism.%20Opinion%20polls%20consistently%20showed%20Labour%20significantly%20ahead%20of%20the%20Tories%2C%20which%20reflected%20the%20public%20mood%20that%20was%20in%20favour%20of%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EMainstreaming%20The%20Far-Right%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERN's%20rise%20cannot%20be%20attributed%20solely%20to%20the%20mistakes%20of%20Mr%20Macron.%20Ms%20Le%20Pen's%20deliberate%20efforts%20to%20soften%20the%20party's%20image%20have%20been%20instrumental.%20Since%20inheriting%20leadership%20from%20her%20father%2C%20Jean-Marie%20Le%20Pen%2C%20in%202011%2C%20she%20has%20worked%20to%20shed%20the%20party's%20extreme-right%20reputation.%20The%202018%20rebranding%20from%20the%20National%20Front%20to%20the%20National%20Rally%20marked%20a%20significant%20step%20in%20this%20transformation.%20In%20a%20decisive%20move%20to%20break%20from%20the%20past%2C%20Ms%20Le%20Pen%20expelled%20her%20father%20from%20the%20party%20in%202015%20following%20his%20repetition%20of%20a%20contentious%20Holocaust%20remark.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20party%20did%20not%20shake%20off%20its%20xenophobic%20rhetoric.%20Jordan%20Bardella%2C%20the%20party's%20would-be%20prime%20minister%2C%20has%20vowed%20to%20bar%20dual%20nationals%20from%20several%20state%20jobs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EReflections%20For%20Conservative%20Party%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20electoral%20result%2C%20the%20worst%20for%20the%20Tories%20since%201906%2C%20brought%20home%20deep%20differences%20among%20the%20party%20ranks.%20party%20leaders%20such%20as%20Suella%20Braverman%20and%20Penny%20Mordaunt%20have%20criticised%20the%20failure%20of%20the%20party%20to%20connect%20with%20voters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20want%20to%20briefly%20address%20the%20results%20around%20the%20country%2C%20and%20there's%20only%20one%20thing%20I%20can%20say...%20sorry.%20I'm%20sorry.%20The%20Great%20British%20people%20voted%20for%20us%20over%2014%20years%20and%20we%20did%20not%20keep%20our%20promises...%20we%20acted%20like%20we%20were%20entitled%20to%20your%20votes%2C%26quot%3B%20Ms%20Braverman%20said%20as%20quoted%20by%20the%20BBC.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20sorry%20my%20party%20didn't%20listen%20to%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20also%20uncertainty%20in%20which%20direction%20the%20Tories%20will%20take%20in%20the%20future%2C%20with%20calls%20for%20a%20more%20coherent%20policy%20to%20gain%20back%20the%20trust%20of%20the%20voters.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720171560000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-07%2Ff7navm1g_macron-sunak-_625x300_05_July_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fuk-elections-france-elections-tale-of-two-elections-how-voters-in-uk-france-turned-on-their-leaders-6039613%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Elections%20in%20both%20the%20United%20Kingdom%20and%20France%20reflected%20voter%20discontent.%20While%20France%20has%20see